  "text": "This difference can be explained by the known interaction between years of education and performance involving several cognitive-linguistic tasks, such as episodic memory, attention, reading, vocabulary and executive functions. In a recent study, scores on the questions from the \"qualities of hearing\" subscale were found to correlate with years of education [CITATION_1] . Because the present investigation was a pilot study, it did not seek to analyze the influence of non-auditory aspects, such as participants´ education, age or socioeconomic level, on SSQ performance, although it recognizes the influence of these factors on the scores attained in the groups assessed. Validation of an instrument is an ongoing process and so investigation of these aspects is important, especially since the Brazilian population is highly heterogeneous.",
